# Understanding Python `.venv`, Requests,, and FastAPI 

## Big Rule

Use `python3` only to create the `.venv`.

After `.venv` exists, use the project Python:

```bash
.venv/bin/python
```

Meaning:

```bash
python3
```

means whatever Python your computer finds globally.

```bash
.venv/bin/python
```

means the Python inside this project.

For this project, prefer:

```bash
.venv/bin/python -m pip install ...
.venv/bin/python -m pytest
.venv/bin/python -m uvicorn ...
.venv/bin/python app/cli/cli.main.py
```

